function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses Julia's `filter` function along with an anonymous function to filter the list `words`. The anonymous function `w -> isuppercase(w[1])` checks if the first character of each word `w` is an uppercase letter using `isuppercase`. The `filter` function keeps only those elements of `words` for which the anonymous function returns `true`.
